Citigroup to Add Nine Emerging Nations to Bond Market Indexes

-- B y   L i l i a n   K a r u n u n g a n
-- 
2011-09-16T08:00:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/citigroup-to-add-nine-emerging-nations-to-bond-market-indexes.html
Citigroup Inc. will add nine
emerging-market countries to its local-currency government bond
indexes, citing the growing appetite for such benchmarks.  Debt from the Czech Republic, Hungary, Turkey, Israel,
 South Africa ,  Brazil , Chile, Colombia and Peru will be included,
Thomas Klaffky, New York-based managing director at the bank
said in a statement today. The U.S. bank will also launch two
regional government bond indexes: the Central and Eastern
Europe, Middle East and Africa Government Bond Index, and the
Latin America Government Bond Index.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lilian Karunungan in Singapore at 
 lkarunungan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sandy Hendry at 
 shendry@bloomberg.net  